Approximately 50 people were injured in a chemical gas explosion at a business on Industry Street in Olifantsfontein on Friday morning. ER24 medics arrived at the scene at 07:10 and found that the business had already been evacuated. "Medical services set up a triage area and began to tend to the patients," ER24 spokesperson Russell Meiring said in a statement on Friday. "Assessments showed that approximately 50 people had sustained minor to moderate injuries. Fortunately, no serious injuries or fatalities were found on the scene." WATCH: Drone footage shows Worcester blast aftermath Drone footage taken in Worcester during the early hours of Wednesday has revealed the aftermath of the gas explosion that rocked the Western Cape town. READ: Worcester gas explosion victim recovering from burn wounds in hospital People were treated for injuries and transported by various services to nearby hospitals for further medical care. The cause of the explosion was not yet known, but local authorities were investigating. News24 contacted EMS spokesperson, Robert Mulaudzi for comment. It will be added once received. GET THE NEWS at your fingertips and download the News24 app for Android here now. Get it for your iPhone here. KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW News24 on Twitter 